(959, 'onlinecourseportal', 'Dementia refers to an acquired and progressive loss of mental functions due to a brain disorder. Dementia is not a specific\n			disease. It is an overall term that describes a wide range of symptoms associated with a decline in memory or other thinking skills \n			severe enough to reduce a person''s ability to perform everyday activities. A medical diagnosis is required to determine the underlying 			cause or causes of symptoms.'),
